The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular and XOS functions, which are commonly studied in the areas of algorithms and optimization (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing the adaptivity gap between adaptive and non-adaptive strategies, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT).
